• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The World Health Organisation says South Africa is one of the countries at risk of possibly having plague cases. Trade and travel links with Madagascar is what puts South Africa at risk. READ: Madagascar plague death toll climbs to 124 The outbreak has already killed 124 people in Madagascar and infected more than 1,100 people. The National Institute for Communicable Diseases briefed the media on the impact of the outbreak on South Africa. No cases have been exported from Madagascar and measures are in place to reduce infections. Facts about the plague outbreak by Estelle Bronkhorst eNCA